  <summary date="2015-07-27T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Homeless and Foster Youth Achievement Act

This bill amends the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 to require a state to include additional information&#160;in its annual state report card.&#160;

Under current law, a state must&#160;include&#160;data regarding student achievement&#160;on state academic assessments,&#160;both in the aggregate and disaggregated by race, ethnicity, disability status, migrant status, English proficiency, and status as&#160;disadvantaged.&#160; For purposes of a state's annual report card, the bill expands those categories to include homeless status and status as a child in foster care. Graduation rates for secondary school students must be reported by the same categories by which student achievement data is reported.</summary>
